  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across 5 flow-speed combinations. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels fall below required levels in 7 factors, and 6 factors are flagged as epistemic gaps. The hemolysis sub-model parameterisation relies on the power-law damage accumulation coefficients reported in the primary reference (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003), which is cited via referencesIdentifier but is not resolved as a typed node within this package graph. Decision: Accepted (conditional on sponsor commitment to close factor gaps prior to PMA submission).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Low",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-mrl5",
